               <p>ANTHONY HAGMIRE. I am a <rs id="t18280911-357-viclabel1841" type="occupation">pork-butcher</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-357-victim1930 t18280911-357-viclabel1841"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18280911-357-crimeloc1842">Ratcliff-highway</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-357-crimeloc1842" type="placeName" value="Ratcliff-highway"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-357-crimeloc1842" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-357-off1839 t18280911-357-crimeloc1842"></join>. I lost a loin of pork on the 9th of August; I was just outside the door - I went after the prisoner and found the pork on him; he had got about ten yards - it was my pork; he said he would pay for it, and at the watch-house he pulled some money out - he said before the Magistrate that he had never been in the shop.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-357-person1931">
                  ELIZABETH 
                  STALL
               <interp inst="t18280911-357-person1931" type="surname" value="STALL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-357-person1931" type="given" value="ELIZABETH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-357-person1931" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am servant to Mr. Hagmire. I saw the prisoner come and take this pork from the window - he came into the shop, and stood a few minutes, as if to have it weighed; he then went out with it, and I told Mr. Hagmire, who followed him; it was about ten o'clock on Saturday night - when I saw him go out I got under the flap and followed him.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I never was in the shop.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18280911-357-verdict1843" type="verdictDescription">
